{"topicSections":[{"title":"Face driving","identifiers":["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitFaceDriver","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitToVRMMapper","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/PerfectSyncCapability","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/PerfectSyncMapper","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitFaceBlendShapes"],"anchor":"Face-driving"},{"title":"Body driving","identifiers":["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitBodyDriver","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitBodySkeleton","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitJoint","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitCoordinateConverter"],"anchor":"Body-driving"},{"title":"Smoothing","identifiers":["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SmoothingFilter","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SmoothingConfig","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SkeletonSmoothingConfig"],"anchor":"Smoothing"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/vrmmetalkit\/arkitintegration"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"ARKit","identifiers":["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitFaceDriver","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/DriverStatistics","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SourcePriorityStrategy","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitToVRMMapper","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/BlendShapeFormula","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/PerfectSyncMapper","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/PerfectSyncCapability","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/PerfectSyncCapability\/DetectionResult","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitBodyDriver","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitBodyDriver\/Statistics","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitBodyDriver\/SourcePriority","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitSkeletonMapper","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitCoordinateConverter","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARMetadataSource","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARFaceSource"],"anchor":"ARKit","generated":true}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit"],["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/AnimationAndRetargeting"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Drive a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/VRMModel","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" from ","type":"text"},{"code":"ARFaceAnchor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"ARBodyAnchor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" data using the face and body drivers.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitIntegration","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"VRMMetalKit’s ARKit support is split into two independent drivers. ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitFaceDriver","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" consumes an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitFaceBlendShapes","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" snapshot and writes weights into a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/VRMExpressionController","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitBodyDriver","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" consumes an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitBodySkeleton","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and writes parent-relative local rotations into your model’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/VRMNode","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" array. Neither driver owns an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ARSession"},{"type":"text","text":" — you feed them the data, they retarget it. That separation lets you drive a VRM from a live "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ARSessionDelegate"},{"type":"text","text":", a recorded file, or a remote iPhone over Wi-Fi without changing the renderer-side wiring."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Smoothing is a separate concern, configured per-driver via "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SmoothingConfig"},{"type":"text","text":" (face) and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SkeletonSmoothingConfig"},{"type":"text","text":" (body). Both drivers also reject stale data: if the snapshot’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"timestamp"},{"type":"text","text":" is older than 150 ms the update is skipped, which keeps a dropped frame from latching a frozen pose."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Driving facial expression","anchor":"Driving-facial-expression"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After loading the model, call ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitFaceDriver\/initializeForModel(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" once to detect Perfect Sync — if the VRM ships custom expressions named after ARKit blend shapes, the driver routes the full 52-shape signal through them; otherwise the default ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitToVRMMapper","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" produces the 18 standard VRM keys (5 emotion, 5 viseme, 3 blink, 4 look, neutral). No input shape is silently dropped; unmapped shapes still contribute to the neutral weight.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import ARKit","import VRMMetalKit","","let faceDriver = ARKitFaceDriver(smoothing: .default)","faceDriver.initializeForModel(model)            \/\/ model: VRMModel","","\/\/ In ARSessionDelegate:","func session(_ session: ARSession, didUpdate anchors: [ARAnchor]) {","    guard let face = anchors.compactMap({ $0 as? ARFaceAnchor }).first else { return }","","    var shapes: [String: Float] = [:]","    for (key, value) in face.blendShapes {","        shapes[key.rawValue] = value.floatValue","    }","    let snapshot = ARKitFaceBlendShapes(","        timestamp: CACurrentMediaTime(),","        shapes: shapes,","        headTransform: face.transform","    )","    faceDriver.update(blendShapes: snapshot, controller: expressionController)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Driving body pose","anchor":"Driving-body-pose"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ARSkeleton3D"},{"type":"text","text":" exposes joint transforms in two spaces: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"jointModelTransforms"},{"type":"text","text":" (anchor-relative) and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"jointLocalTransforms"},{"type":"text","text":" (parent-relative). The body driver expects "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"world space","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", so compose "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"anchor.transform * jointModelTransform"},{"type":"text","text":" before populating the dictionary. Passing anchor-relative transforms directly will rotate the avatar relative to the room instead of relative to the camera, which is almost never what you want."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let bodyDriver = ARKitBodyDriver(smoothing: .default)","","func session(_ session: ARSession, didUpdate anchors: [ARAnchor]) {","    guard let body = anchors.compactMap({ $0 as? ARBodyAnchor }).first else { return }","    let skeleton3D = body.skeleton","","    var joints: [ARKitJoint: simd_float4x4] = [:]","    for jointName in skeleton3D.definition.jointNames {","        guard let mapped = ARKitJoint(rawValue: jointName),","              let model = skeleton3D.modelTransform(for: .init(rawValue: jointName)) else { continue }","        joints[mapped] = body.transform * model        \/\/ compose to world space","    }","","    let snapshot = ARKitBodySkeleton(","        timestamp: CACurrentMediaTime(),","        joints: joints,","        isTracked: true","    )","    bodyDriver.update(skeleton: snapshot, nodes: model.nodes, humanoid: model.humanoid)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The driver does parent-relative local rotation, A-pose-to-T-pose offsets, left-side mirroring (via ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitCoordinateConverter","type":"reference"},{"text":"), SLERP smoothing, and NaN rejection. It does ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" use Graham-Schmidt orthogonalization.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Smoothing","anchor":"Smoothing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Filter selection lives on "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SmoothingConfig","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (face, per-expression) and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SkeletonSmoothingConfig","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (body, separate position\/rotation\/scale filters). Pick "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SmoothingFilter\/none","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for impulse-like signals such as blinks, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SmoothingFilter\/ema(alpha:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for low-cost smoothing of continuous signals (the default — alpha around 0.3 for face, 0.2 for body rotation), and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SmoothingFilter\/kalman(processNoise:measurementNoise:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" when you have time to tune Q\/R against captured data. Per-case selection is documented on the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/SmoothingFilter","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" symbol page."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Coordinate handedness","level":2,"anchor":"Coordinate-handedness","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitCoordinateConverter","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" handles the right-handed-Y-up (ARKit) to left-handed-Y-up (VRM) conversion plus left-side mirroring. Most callers never touch it directly; the body driver invokes it internally. If you are debugging a mirror artifact on a single limb, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARKitCoordinateConverter\/leftSideJoints","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"API Collection","title":"ARKit Integration","modules":[{"name":"VRMMetalKit"}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"references":{"doc://VRMMetalKit/documentation/VRMMetalKit/ARMetadataSource":{"url":"\/documentation\/vrmmetalkit\/armetadatasource","title":"ARMetadataSource","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ARMetadataSource","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ARMetadataSource","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ARMetadataS